0000 = 0
0001 = 1
0010 = 2
0011 = 3
0100 = 4
0101 = 5
0110 = 6
0111 = 7
1000 = 8
1001 = 9
1010 = A
1011 = B
1100 = C
1101 = D
1110 = E
1111 = F
0xNN

1) PORTX to pre-set desired output values and use no pullups for the "to-be" inputs
2) DDRX now set direction (outputs reflect desired values) and no pullups active
3) PORTX to re-state desired outputs but now turn on pullups for desired inputs
